In the book, you quote
Mrs. Fleming as saying that

00:53:08.030 --> 00:53:11.780
women's patience, perseverance,
and method in many things were

00:53:11.780 --> 00:53:13.310
superior to men's.

00:53:13.310 --> 00:53:15.179
So having done
all this research,

00:53:15.179 --> 00:53:16.220
what do you make of that?

00:53:16.220 --> 00:53:17.150
Was it true then?

00:53:17.150 --> 00:53:18.320
Is it true now?

00:53:18.320 --> 00:53:21.620
- Well, she thought it was true.

00:53:21.620 --> 00:53:27.590
And some people felt that women
actually had better pattern

00:53:27.590 --> 00:53:29.630
recognition skills.

00:53:29.630 --> 00:53:32.554
Maria Mitchell is on
record as saying--

00:53:32.554 --> 00:53:34.220
I'm going to mangle
this quote, but it's

00:53:34.220 --> 00:53:39.320
something like the hand
that guides the needle helps

00:53:39.320 --> 00:53:43.970
the eye of the telescope,
that the skills that girls

00:53:43.970 --> 00:53:47.840
were taught in her day actually
made them better observers.

00:53:47.840 --> 00:53:50.510
I have no evidence
for that, but it

00:53:50.510 --> 00:53:54.020
was something people thought.

00:53:54.020 --> 00:53:58.520
The big complaint Mrs. Fleming
had was not being paid enough.

00:53:58.520 --> 00:54:04.130
And that was the downside of the
wonderful opportunity they had.

00:54:04.130 --> 00:54:07.580
And I think as forward
thinking and broadminded

00:54:07.580 --> 00:54:11.690
as Pickering was, he knew he
was getting a bargain because he

00:54:11.690 --> 00:54:13.582
could hire the
women more cheaply.

