here studying physics.

01:03:29.510 --> 01:03:32.930
And I was just curious about
your comment about the person

01:03:32.930 --> 01:03:34.550
on the other end.

01:03:34.550 --> 01:03:36.290
I'm finding your story
very interesting.

01:03:36.290 --> 01:03:38.780
And I'm wondering if there's
a message or a lesson

01:03:38.780 --> 01:03:42.320
that you'd like this generation
of astronomy and physics

01:03:42.320 --> 01:03:44.510
students, both male and
female, to take away

01:03:44.510 --> 01:03:48.980
from the story of the ladies
in the Harvard Observatory.

01:03:48.980 --> 01:03:52.910
- Not a message, no.

01:03:52.910 --> 01:03:55.820
I don't remember who said
this, but it's a famous line,

01:03:55.820 --> 01:04:00.210
if you want to send a
message, call Western Union.

01:04:00.210 --> 01:04:06.690
But just the story itself
that it was forgotten.

01:04:06.690 --> 01:04:07.890
And it's a great story.

01:04:07.890 --> 01:04:14.130
And I think it's good for a
lot of young people in science

01:04:14.130 --> 01:04:16.268
to know about what
happened here.

01:04:19.720 --> 01:04:20.220
- Hi.

01:04:20.220 --> 01:04:22.100
I'm Bulbul Chakraborty.

01:04:22.100 --> 01:04:23.240
I'm a physicist.

01:04:23.240 --> 01:04:26.590
I am a professor at Brandeis.

01:04:26.590 --> 01:04:29.530
In physics, astronomy
astrophysics

01:04:29.530 --> 01:04:33.550
has many more women
than physics in general.

01:04:33.550 --> 01:04:35.870
And what I didn't
know is that there

01:04:35.870 --> 01:04:39.700
was this special fellowship
that Pickering had,

01:04:39.700 --> 01:04:44.650
which recruited
women to go into PhD.

01:04:44.650 --> 01:04:49.540
And it almost seems to me after
being around these many years

01:04:49.540 --> 01:04:52.470
that you almost need
a catalyst like that

01:04:52.470 --> 01:04:57.700
to balance out the numbers.

01:04:57.700 --> 01:05:00.070
A biologist colleague
of mine told me

01:05:00.070 --> 01:05:02.710
that that's what happened
in the life sciences

01:05:02.710 --> 01:05:06.850
in the '60s when men
were drafted for the war

01:05:06.850 --> 01:05:09.670
and women were readily
taken into labs.

01:05:09.670 --> 01:05:14.080
And then people started
appreciating what women did.

01:05:14.080 --> 01:05:17.020
It seems to me that the
Pickering Fellowship

01:05:17.020 --> 01:05:21.100
did that same thing for
astrophysicists and women

01:05:21.100 --> 01:05:26.230
astronomers hasn't
happened in physics.

01:05:26.230 --> 01:05:29.790
- I think we need to
find somebody like that

01:05:29.790 --> 01:05:32.820
who cam make it happen.

01:05:32.820 --> 01:05:34.940
- I had one more
question, comment.

01:05:34.940 --> 01:05:36.450
So when I came to
graduate school,

01:05:36.450 --> 01:05:39.000
I was a graduate
student at Stonybrook.

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:41.460
And there used to be
a room full of women

01:05:41.460 --> 01:05:45.080
who used to look at bubble
chamber photographs.

01:05:45.080 --> 01:05:47.610
And it was a completely
different population.

01:05:47.610 --> 01:05:52.040
We as women PhD students
never talked to them.

01:05:52.040 --> 01:05:55.510
I don't think I ever
talked to any of them.

01:05:55.510 --> 01:05:58.450
And in later years
I had thought,

01:05:58.450 --> 01:06:01.230
it was just a complete--

01:06:01.230 --> 01:06:05.680
I we didn't think they
were doing science.

01:06:05.680 --> 01:06:08.340
They were never part
of the department.

01:06:08.340 --> 01:06:10.100
They were never--

01:06:10.100 --> 01:06:16.930
- Well, I think there's a
tendency among women as much

01:06:16.930 --> 01:06:22.580
as some men to feel that if
women are doing that work,

01:06:22.580 --> 01:06:26.140
it can't be that difficult
or that important.

01:06:26.140 --> 01:06:28.900
And--

01:06:28.900 --> 01:06:32.380
- It was just that importance
was never made clear to us.

01:06:32.380 --> 01:06:35.710
And I sort of now in
retrospect blame the faculty

01:06:35.710 --> 01:06:38.782
for not doing that
in some sense.

01:06:42.010 --> 01:06:43.450
I don't know what they did.

01:06:43.450 --> 01:06:46.090
I still don't know
what they did.

01:06:46.090 --> 01:06:48.200
- Well, someone is
writing a book about them.

01:06:48.200 --> 01:06:50.220
So you'll find out.

